{% raw %}
# Character-by-character timing attack
# Non-constant-time string comparison leaks password length/chars

# Attack flow:
1. Measure response time for password of different lengths
2. Identify length where timing changes (correct length)
3. For each position, test characters measuring timing
4. Longer time = more characters matched before failure

# Target functions:
- strcmp/memcmp (non-constant time)
- Early-exit loops
- Database lookups with partial matching
